OL,3,CMum shares grief over second Christmas
OL,4,Cwithout her son's murder being solved
OL,6,F"And then there's that moment each
OL,7,Fmorning ` when we open our eyes and
OL,8,Ffor just a second we forget. Then it
OL,9,Fhits. That tidal wave of pain, trauma,
OL,10,Fand grief crashes over us and takes
OL,11,Four breath away all over again.
OL,13,F"Simple things are so hard now. We all
OL,14,Fjust crave to see your face or hear
OL,15,Fyour voice one more time. Just once."
OL,17,FCarolyn added that the pain of her
OL,18,Floss is "unbearable."
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/6
